title: cached
extract: In computing, a cache (/kæʃ/ kash, or /ˈkeɪʃ/ kaysh in AuE) is a hardware or software component that stores data so that future requests for that data can be served faster; the data stored in a cache might be the result of an earlier computation or a copy of data stored elsewhere.
